com.samysadi.acs.hardware.misc

Class MetaData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.samysadi.acs.hardware.misc.MetaData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable

    public class MetaData
extends Object
implements Cloneable
    This class contains meta data of a memory zone.
    Especially, it contains a data identifier to uniquely identify the data contained inside of that memory zone. This data identifier is the equivalent to the path used for uniquely identifying a file inside a file-system.

    You can test if a MetaData is describing the same data using the method isSameData(MetaData).

    This class only allows you to set basic meta-data. You are free to create subclasses to add extra fields.

    1.0

    • Method Detail

      • clone

        public MetaData clone()
        This method creates and returns a copy of the current meta-data using the Object.clone() method.

        The newly created meta-data instance will contain the same data identifier as the current instance. In other words, the two instances will be describing the same data.

        The Bitmap is also cloned.

        Overrides:
        clone in class Object
        Returns:
        the newly created MetaData

      • getVersionId

        public long getVersionId()
        Return a long that contains the version number of the data related to this MetaData. This long should be modified accordingly to reflect changes on the data that is related to this MetaData.
        Returns:

        public boolean isSameData(MetaData metaData)
